<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">Features</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
    <ListItem>
        <Paragraph>Supports automatic segment count.</Paragraph>
    </ListItem>

    <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Supports both clockwise and counterclockwise rolling.</Paragraph>
    </ListItem>

</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">Interactive Features</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Specify the type of rolling gauge to be used by selecting the Enable Numeric Values check box.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
	
	 <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Specify the value of a rolling gauge by selecting the Value text box.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>

        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Specify numeric gauge value in the Value field.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem> 

	<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Specify the number of characters to be displayed on the rolling gauge by using the Segment Count text box.</Paragraph>
	</ListItem>


	<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Specify the rolling direction of segments on the gauge by using the Direction combo box.</Paragraph>
	</ListItem>


	<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Use the Minimum Value text box to set the lowest number shown in the numeric gauge.</Paragraph>
	</ListItem>


	<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Use the Maximum Value text box set the highest number shown in the numeric gauge.</Paragraph>
	</ListItem>


	<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Use the Unit text box to specify the type of unit of measure shown in the gauge.</Paragraph>
	</ListItem>


	<ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Specify unit position in the Unit Position combo box.</Paragraph>
	</ListItem>
</List>


</FlowDocument>
